  "summary": "TPC-H SF10 is a parallel analytical workload dominated by full scans of the 60M-row lineitem table. Q1 and Q6 are embarrassingly parallel single-table scans with low-cardinality aggregations (6 and 1 group). Q3 is a three-way join filtered on customer.c_mktsegment=BUILDING (20%) and orders.o_orderdate (8%), with parallelism on the final lineitem scan yielding 5M aggregation groups—the critical optimization lever is early predicate pushdown (filter customer before joining orders) and morsel-driven parallel execution (64 cores available). With 376GB memory, all intermediate joins fit in RAM; disk I/O (HDD, not SSD) is secondary concern for this prototype. Key techniques: vectorized filtering (SIMD), parallel hash aggregation with per-morsel pre-aggregation, hash joins on FK relationships, and thread-safe morsel queues."
